
[1]contumelious

   CONTUMELIOUS, a. [L. See Contumely.]

   1. Haughtily reproachful; contemptuous; insolent; rude and sarcastic;
   as contumelious language.

   2. Haughty and contemptuous; disposed to utter reproach, or to insult;
   insolent; proudly rude; as a contumelious person.

   3. Reproachful; shameful; ignominious.
